CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 17, 1950, pg. 7 reads: "Republicans Elect Chairman In Fifth Ward - ...extreme left, William Ackerman and Curtis B. Haines are...discussing the proxy of Margaret Sullivan, commit-...of the Ninth District, which had been turned over...Haines. Ackerman persuaded Mrs. Ackerman, who...to attend the meeting, kept her seated in an auto...in front of the Leo Weil School until the election got under way.  Then she appeared in person, demanded return...and voted for David A. Thompkins, who defeated George L. Winstead, 54-44."
TitMainTitle: William Ackerman and Curtis B. Haines standing in A. Leo Weil school auditorium for Fifth Ward elections
